<head>BOTH</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">倆</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>ALL of TWO THINGS. [GRAMMAR]</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current binary universal quantifier is liǎng 兩, which can quantify both subjects and objects.</p>
<p>2. Shuāng 雙 is much rarer, and the word never quantifies the object so that the word is marginal in the group.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>倆</p>
<p>雙方</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
    </div>
